&gt; ... when you have a pointer to memory bound to one type and you need to access that memory as instances of another type. 

Example: Take the address of the general struct, then rebind and dereference the pointer:

    let general = GeneralStruct()

    let specific = withUnsafePointer(to: general) {
        $0.withMemoryRebound(to: SpecificStruct.self, capacity: 1) {
            $0.pointee
        }
    }

If both types have the same size and a compatible memory layout then you can also use [`unsafeBitCast(_:to:)`](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swift/1641250-unsafebitcast):

&gt; Use this function only to convert the instance passed as x to a layout-compatible type when conversion through other means is not possible.

